Start with the documentation available on the jMock web site:
http://www.jmock.org/docs.html
 
You'll definitely want to read the Getting Started guide
(http://www.jmock.org/getting-started.html), and since you want to mock
a class you'll want to read the document about mocking classes
(typically people mock interfaces) at http://www.jmock.org/cglib.html.
 
If after reading those you still aren't sure what to do, then I'd
suggest sending your request to the jMock users mailing list.
 
..David..

Hello, 

I am having the following code

class New {
       public void f1() {
              int a = f2();
        }
       public int f2() {
              // some code 

               return a;
        }
}

I want to know whether f2() is being called in f1() or not using jmock
Please guide me to implement this using jmock.
